t mobile suits, that works.  Mechs for industrial purposes, that works, mechs for lawn gardening.....wait.....nevermind.<br><br>But seriously, a mech like the one in Aliens: 2, would be vary helpful.  At least I think.  Especally in something like a car wreck (Just had one the other day, everything is kinda geared on that subject), or in a collapsed building, where cranes would have a harder time getting to a certain point and grasping the required girder/part, a pair of mechs could have a fairly easy time moving a car from a person trapped beneath.<br><br>Expensive:  For now, yeah.<br><br>But, like with drawing, practice makes perfect.  Juat look at the modern car.  Alot better than waht there used to be, in most ways.<br><br>So for now, mechs arent that great.  But if someone doesnt try and start making them now, it wont ever get any better. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/unaokochan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Naoko Chan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Hot Sexy B*tch <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/5/02 4:46:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1265.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://naokochan.xoasis.com/bunnygirl100x68.gif width=100 height=68></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  N</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Also we can assume mechas would be far more maneuverable and faster than tanks<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Please... a mech moving as manuverable like in anime?  In Macross Plus, my teacher (who fought in Vietnam as a pilot) said that the pilots in those Valkaries would be dead from the G forces they go through when he changes direction that fast.  And that Hollywood makes dog fights look easy.  <br><br>Reality sets in when you make mechs.  Physics just makes mechs unrealistic to even make.  Casting reality aside, Raiden took out alot of Metal Gear Rays with just Stinger Missles.  Metal Gears Rays are not cost effective if mere Stinger missles could take them out.<br><br><br>N <p><img src=http://naokochan.xoasis.com/sig.gif><BR><B>Kaba wa shinanakya naoranai.</B><BR><a href=http://pub50.ezboard.com/bnaokochansidiosyncraticoutofplaceplace>Naoko Chan's Idiosyncratic OUT OF PLACE Place</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugrandmasterniw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>grandmaster NIW</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/5/02 5:04:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1265.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Will there ever be Mecha?</span><hr size=1>   i think that mechs like in mechwarrior(the kind with chicken legs)  is a great idea, it would be much convenient to climb up rocky mountains than tanks that menouver on wheels.  but one pilot mechs would be awfully hard to come to.  <br>  humanoid mechs also sound like a bad idea, have you ever though of who you would opperate one? how would you come about moving the arms and legs?   and when a mech would reach a certain size, it's own weight would crush it.  think about a mech that has an arm that is 12 tons in weight.  if it were to reach out, the weight of the arm would rip off the arm from it's socket.  think about two of these fighting, the one that pulls off the first TOUCH would win.  not even mentioning the damage it would do to itself if it were